Package p4_group_8_repo.Controllers

Class SelectModelFactory

java.lang.Object
p4_group_8_repo.Controllers.SelectModelFactory
public class SelectModelFactory
extends java.lang.Object
A factory class following the Factory Design Pattern. Allows the caller to select which Actor object to instantiate.
This reduces coupling between classes as the caller is not dependent on the class they're calling directly.
If any changes occur to the class being called, the changes will only be reflected on the factory class while the caller remains in the unknown about it.

  • Method Details

    • getActor

      public Actor getActor​(int actor, int x, int y, int dim, int s, int n)
      Instantiates different Actor objects that don't need any image setting in their constructor.
      Instantiates End, Digit, Turtle and WetTurtle objects depending on the client class' selection.
      Parameters:
      actor - choice of actor. 1 for End, 2 for Digit, 3 for Turtle and 4 for WetTurtle.
      x - x position of the object
      y - y position of the object
      dim - dimensions (height and width) of the object's image
      s - speed of the object
      n - number for the Digit object
      Returns:
      Actor object depending on the choice of the client class

    • getAnimal

      public Actor getAnimal()
      Instantiates a new Animal object. Animal object is instantiated in its own method as it doesn't require any parameters.
      Returns:
      Animal object

    • getActorWithImage

      public Actor getActorWithImage​(java.lang.String imageLink, int x, int y, double s, int dim)
      Instantiates different Actor objects that need image setting in their constructor.
      Instantiates Log and Obstacle objects depending on the client class' selection.
      Parameters:
      imageLink - imageLink of the object's image
      x - x position of the object
      y - y position of the object
      s - speed of the object
      dim - dimensions (width and height) of the object's image
      Returns:
      either a Log or an Obstacle object depending on choice by the client class
